  "vulnerability_information": "The (1) EPHEMERAL, (2) HTTPS, (3) MVG, (4) MSL, (5) TEXT, (6) SHOW, (7) WIN, and (8) PLT coders in ImageMagick before 6.9.3-10 and 7.x before 7.0.1-1 allow remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via shell metacharacters in a crafted image, aka \"ImageTragick.\" \n\nSee also: \nhttp://www.openwall.com/lists/oss-security/2016/05/03/18 \nhttps://imagetragick.com/\n",
